These 5 mounted illustrations by Mildred Codding may have been used in the production of 
                        Meningiomas
                      or appear in the monograph, but their exact locations in the text are unknown. Item-level descriptions: 
small illustration of a tumor in pencil, mounted on 2 layers of cardboard; 
4-part illustration, detached from board, with labels reading "Frontal lobe," "Sella turcica," and "calcified area"; 
mounted illustration labeled "Endicott," "glio-chias." (?), "Fig. 16 Do not reduce," and on back: "Endicott 13340," "Vol. 8"; 
mounted illustration of a brain labeled "Anna Simpson," "para," with text on illustration reading "Old bone flap"; 
mounted illustration, no patient name or identifier, with text on illustration reading "Chiasma," "A. Carotis," "N. Oculomotor."
